Program: Last Word
Title: Omar Sharif, Stanley 'Steve' Moore, Jules Wright, Yevgeny Primakov, Ernest Tomlinson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0612wdk
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 12 Jul 2015
Matthew Bannister on Actor Omar Sharif Flying squad detective Stanley Moore - always known as Steve, he helped to catch some of the Great Train Robbers. Theatre Director Jules Wright who co-founded the Women's Playhouse Trust and set up the Wapping Project arts venue. Former Russian Foreign and Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov. And the composer Ernest Tomlinson, best known for his light orchestral works. Show less